-- Deutsche Bank’s Postbank to Stop Wealth Management, NDR Reports
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2012-04-27T17:48:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/deutsche-bank-s-postbank-to-stop-wealth-management-ndr-reports.html
Deutsche Bank AG (DBK) ’s Postbank unit
will discontinue its wealth-management business on June 30
because of a lack of demand,  NDR Info  reported, citing an
unidentified Postbank spokesman.  About 300 employees will be offered positions in mobile
sales for Deutsche Bank and at the construction-financing bank
BHW, NDR Info said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
